Package com.ibm.eznosql

Class ResultSet

java.lang.Object
com.ibm.eznosql.ResultSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ReadUpdateResultSet
public class ResultSet extends Object implements AutoCloseable
This class represents a positioning into the database. A ResultSet is returned from Connection.read(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) and Connection.readGeneric(java.lang.String, java.lang.String), or Connection.readOneForUpdate(java.lang.String, java.lang.String). Note that positioning may contain results which do not match the requested result, but it is guaranteed that the results are ordered according to the search key.

    • close

      public void close() throws IllegalStateException, EzNoSQLException
      Ends positioning into the EzNoSQL database previously obtained by the Connection.read(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) or Connection.readGeneric(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) ResultSet methods. Any resources associated with the ResultSet instance are freed, and for non-recoverable databases, any document level locks will be released. This method is invoked automatically on objects managed by the try-with-resources statement.
      Specified by:
      close in interface AutoCloseable
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - If the Connection instance or resultToken field is invalid (i.e. already closed)
      EzNoSQLException - If the call returned an error, see class for detailed usage and error handling.
